title: For Sale:  Tri Star 9MM Pistol 17 Round mags
postcontent: This isn’t a CZ75, but it’s awfully close. Where the CZ75 is all steel and pretty heavy, This L120’s alloy frame renders the gross weight 28 ounces empty. Turkish guns are here to stay, and this one is remarkably well made  Its price competition to both Baby Eagles and parent CZs themselves will at least make ripples in the market. Design, of course, descends from John M. Browning’s 1935 Hi-Power. Importer is Tri Star of North KC, MO. Type is traditional single and double action blowback semi-automatic. Construction is steel barrel, slide, and internal parts all on a lightweight alloy frame. Barrel is 4 1/2 inch 6 groove, with pressed in barrel bushing. Slide to frame fit is excellent, with full contact rail that runs the length of the frame. Sights are classic CZ style three dot configuration, dovetailed rear sight and rivet secured modified partridge front, 6 1/2 inch sight radius with serrated rib on the slide. Hammer is .212 serrated skeleton Commander type, with .312 smooth face combat trigger. This pistol has a firing pin safety and main safety for right handed shooters. Lever safety will engage in all three hammer positions: full rest, half cock, and fully cocked for secure carry and single action cocked-and-locked readiness. Trigger guard configuration is SP01 type square serrated front face, and the grip frame is serrated fore and aft. Grip panels are hard grainy polymer with the T Tri Star logo. Magazines furnished are Mec-Gar CZ7517B, not catalogued but produced for Tri-Star exclusively in a bright blue finish. This is an excellent pistol. Fit and finish are excellent. Similar pistols from the parent CZ manufacturer command pricing upwards of $700 apiece.

The Cold Hammer Forging process Work Hardens the steel around a rifled mandrel, which creates the lands and grooves. This barrel are chambered in 5.56 NATO, with a 1/7 Twist Rate. The barrel blanks are the correct Certified CMV material and they are also Hard Chrome lined to the M249 SAW Mil-Spec, which is almost twice as thick as the Hard Chrome on a Mil-Spec M4. The End Result is a Light Weight Rifle that can be Run Hard Day after Day! Each barrel is HPT and MPI. They have Mil-Spec M4 barrel extensions, Mil-Spec Phosphate finish on the outside. 

questions? feel free to ask.
